title: Ep. - 345 - CREATORS OF TOP CHEF AND NAILED IT REVIEW OF SEEKING SISTER WIVES
description:
Jo Sharon and Casey Kriley, co-CEOS of Magical Elves, discuss the origin story of their Emmy-nominated series “Nailed It!” and Top Chef. Nailed It is a comedy-first, cooking-second genre-breaking series, where home bakers impossibly complex concept cakes to bake, with hilariously bad results. Top Chef features chefs competing against each other in culinary challenges. They are judged by a panel of professional chefs and other notables from the food and wine industry with one or more contestants eliminated in each episode. 

 

Lauren and Chanler, sisters and co-hosts of the Pop Apologists podcast review Seeking Sister, the TLC reality TV series about the lives of polygamist families.
